ly in analog and digital modes, and how cosmic zoom media has influenced scientific and popular views of the world. Analyzing literature, film, digital media, and database history, Horton establishes a much-needed framework for thinking about scale across multiple domains and disciplines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aScale (Philosophy) 0aScale (Philosophy). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEames.  aanalog.  acosmic zoom.  adatabase.  adigital.  aecology.  amedia.  amediation.  ascalar difference.  ascale.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226742588423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226742588/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles